docs.name: Signal Information & Communication Corp (099830)
docs.description: Signal Information & Communication Corp. is a Korea-based company principally engaged in the provision of network consulting and system integrated services. The Company operates in four businesses: wireless telecommunication solution business, which provides design, construction, maintenance and support services for trunked radio system (TRS) wireless communications networks and wireless broadband (WiBB) solutions; multimedia broadcasting solution business, which provides consulting, design and construction of cable broadcasting networks and distributes cable modems and Internet protocol television (IPTV) terminal units; wired and wireless telecommunication network construction business, which are provided to SKT, KT, GnTel, Motorola and others, as well as telecommunications terminal business, which distributes very high frequency/ultra high frequency (VHF/UHF) radios and related accessories.

docs.name: Latin American Discovery Fund Inc. (LDF)
docs.description: The Latin American Discovery Fund, Inc. (the Fund) is a non-diversified, closed-end management investment company. The Fund's investment objective is long-term capital appreciation through investments primarily in equity securities of Latin American issuers and by investing, from time to time, in debt securities issued or guaranteed by a Latin American government or governmental entity. It invests in various sectors, such as airlines, beverages, chemicals, commercial banks, diversified telecommunication services, food and staples retailing, electric utilities, food products and diversified financial services. The Fund's investment advisor is Morgan Stanley Investment Management Inc. Its sub-advisor is Morgan Stanley Investment Management Limited.

docs.name: DFCEX: Dfa  Emerging Markets Core Equity Portfolio
docs.description:
The investment seeks long-term capital appreciation.
 The fund purchases a broad and diverse group of securities associated with emerging markets, which may include frontier markets (emerging market countries in an earlier stage of development), authorized for investment by the Advisor's Investment Committee ('Approved Markets'), with an increased exposure to securities of small cap issuers and securities that it considers to be value securities. It may gain exposure to companies in Approved Markets by purchasing equity securities in the form of depositary receipts, which may be listed or traded outside the issuer's domicile country.

docs.name: AEMMX: American Century Emerging Markets Fd- A Class
docs.description:

 The fund normally invests at least 80% of its assets in equity securities of companies located in emerging market countries. Under normal market conditions, the fund's portfolio will primarily consist of securities of companies whose earnings or revenues are not only growing, but growing at an accelerating pace.

docs.name: Origo Partners PLC (OPP)
docs.description: Origo Partners Plc (Origo) is a private equity investor and strategic consultancy business, which provides its shareholders with exposure to China-linked investment opportunities. Origo has a portfolio of investments in a range of industrial sectors, including metals and mining, agriculture, renewable energy/clean tech and technology, telecom and media. Origo invests directly in high growth Chinese companies, as well as in companies based around the world with exposure to Chinese export markets.

docs.name: Helix Resources Ltd. (HLX)
docs.description: Helix Resources Limited is an Australia-based company. The Company is a mineral exploration company focused on base metal, gold and iron ore in Australia and Chile. The Company's projects include Restdown Gold Project, Olary Magnetite Project, Canbelego Copper Project, Joshua Copper Project, Huallillinga Copper/Gold Project, Hado Gold/Copper Project, and other projects. The Joshua Project is the Company's advanced project in Chile and is 100% owned with no concession payments or royalties. Huallillinga Project is a 95 square kilometers area with significant potential for shear hosted copper and gold, with little evidence of modern exploration in the district. In February 2013, Lodestone Equities Ltd acquired a 50% interest in Olary Magnetite Pty Ltd (Olary) from the Company. Effective September 13, 2013, Helix Resources Ltd raised its interest to 70% from 51%, by acquiring 19% interest, in Canbelego Joint Venture, from its joint venture partner Straits Resources Ltd.

docs.name: FCSIX: First American High Income Bond Fd Cl C
docs.description:
The investment seeks a high level of current income.
 The fund normally invests at least 80% of net assets in bonds rated lower than investment grade. There is no minimum rating requirement and no limitation on the average maturity or average effective duration of securities held by the fund. It may invest up to 25% of its total assets in dollar denominated debt obligations of foreign corporations and governments.

docs.name: ABWYX: Alliancebernstein Bal Wlth Strategy Adv Cl
docs.description:
The investment seeks to achieve the highest total return consistent with the Adviser's determination of reasonable risk.
 The fund normally invests in a combination of Underlying Portfolios representing a variety of asset classes and investment styles that are also managed by the Adviser. It targets a weighting of approximately 65% of Underlying Portfolios that invest primarily in equity securities and approximately 35% of Underlying Portfolios that invest primarily in debt securities with a goal of providing moderate upside potential without excessive volatility.
